  keywords =     {},
  confidential = {n},
  language =     {en},
  abstract =     {Color image demosaicing consists in recovering full resolution color
information from color-lter-array (CFA) samples with 66.7% amount of miss-
ing data. Most of the existing color demosaicing methods [14, 25, 16, 2, 26]
are based on interpolation from inter-channel correlation and local geometry,
which are not robust to highly saturated color images with small geometric
features. In this paper, we introduce wavelet frame based methods by using
a sparse wavelet [8, 22, 9, 23] approximation of individual color channels and
color differences that recovers both geometric features and color information.
